This paper is about relation classification, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also uses word embeddings and word clusters, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The linear classifier used in the paper is a type of supervised learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions external knowledge sources, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper's focus on developing a high baseline for different relation extraction tasks suggests that it could be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
